cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper introduces a new probabilistic module interface for encapsulating complex probabilistic models with latent variables alongside custom stochastic approximate inference machinery. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of learned stochastic inference networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the construction of sound approximate inference algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
